#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:0.3"
msgid "Pācittiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on confession (_pācittiya_)"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:0.4"
msgid "Musāvādavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 7"

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:0.5"
msgid "7. Dhammadesanāsikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on teaching"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:0.6"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "First sub-story"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-cs-bu-pc7.1, pts-vp-en.2.203, ms2V_197
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā udāyī sāvatthiyaṃ kulūpako hoti, bahukāni kulāni upasaṅkamati."
msgstr "At that time Venerable Udāyī was associating with and visiting a number of families in Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā udāyī pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena aññataraṃ kulaṃ tenupasaṅkami."
msgstr "After robing up one morning, he took his bowl and robe, and went to a certain family."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:1.4"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena gharaṇī nivesanadvāre nisinnā hoti, gharasuṇhā āvasathadvāre nisinnā hoti."
msgstr "Just then the housewife was sitting at the entrance door and the daughter-in-law at the door to one of the rooms."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:1.5"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā udāyī yena gharaṇī tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā gharaṇiyā upakaṇṇake dhammaṃ desesi."
msgstr "Udāyī went up to the housewife and gave her a teaching, whispering in her ear."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:1.6"
msgid "Atha kho gharasuṇhāya etadahosi—"
msgstr "And the daughter-in-law thought,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:1.7"
msgid "“kiṃ nu kho so samaṇo sassuyā jāro udāhu obhāsatī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is this ascetic my mother-in-law’s lover, or is he speaking lewdly?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, pts-vp-pli4.21, ms2V_198
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:1.8"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā udāyī gharaṇiyā upakaṇṇake dhammaṃ desetvā yena gharasuṇhā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā gharasuṇhāya upakaṇṇake dhammaṃ desesi."
msgstr "After teaching the housewife in this way, Udāyī approached the daughter-in-law and gave her a teaching in the same way."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:1.9"
msgid "Atha kho gharaṇiyā etadahosi—"
msgstr "Then the housewife thought,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:1.10"
msgid "“kiṃ nu kho so samaṇo gharasuṇhāya jāro udāhu obhāsatī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is this ascetic my daughter-in-law’s lover, or is he speaking lewdly?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:1.11"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā udāyī gharasuṇhāya upakaṇṇake dhammaṃ desetvā pakkāmi."
msgstr "After giving a teaching in this way, Udāyī left."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:1.12"
msgid "Atha kho gharaṇī gharasuṇhaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "Then the housewife said to her daughter-in-law,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:1.13"
msgid "“he je, kiṃ te eso samaṇo avocā”ti?"
msgstr "“Hey, what did that ascetic say to you?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:1.14"
msgid "“Dhammaṃ me, ayye, desesi”."
msgstr "“He gave me a teaching, Madam."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:1.15"
msgid "“Ayyāya pana kiṃ avocā”ti?"
msgstr "But what did he say to you?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:1.16"
msgid "“Mayhampi dhammaṃ desesī”ti."
msgstr "“He gave me a teaching, too.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-en.2.204
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:1.17"
msgid "Tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "And they complained and criticized him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:1.18"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma ayyo udāyī upakaṇṇake dhammaṃ desessati."
msgstr "“How can Venerable Udāyī give teachings by whispering in the ear?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:1.19"
msgid "Nanu nāma vissaṭṭhena vivaṭena dhammo desetabbo”ti?"
msgstr "Should not teachings be given audibly and openly?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3, ms2V_199
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:1.20"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tāsaṃ itthīnaṃ ujjhāyantīnaṃ khiyyantīnaṃ vipācentīnaṃ."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of those women,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:1.21"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:1.22"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized Udāyī,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:1.23"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma āyasmā udāyī mātugāmassa dhammaṃ desessatī”ti."
msgstr "“How can Venerable Udāyī give teachings to women?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4, ms2V_200
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:1.24"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing him in many ways, they told the Master. …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:1.25"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, udāyi, mātugāmassa dhammaṃ desesī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, Udāyī, that you did this?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:1.26"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:1.27"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:1.28"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, mātugāmassa dhammaṃ desessasi."
msgstr "“… Foolish man, how can you give teachings to women?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:1.29"
msgid "Netaṃ moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:1.30"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:1.30a"
msgid ""
msgstr "First preliminary ruling"

#. HTML: </h3><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc5, ms2V_201
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:1.31"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu mātugāmassa dhammaṃ deseyya pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk gives a teaching to a woman, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p class="endsection">
#. REF: sc6, ms2V_202
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:1.32"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second sub-story"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: sc7, pts-cs-bu-pc7.2, pts-vp-en.2.205, ms2V_203
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena upāsikā bhikkhū passitvā etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards some female lay followers saw some monks and said to them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:2.2"
msgid "“iṅghāyyā, dhammaṃ desethā”ti."
msgstr "“Venerables, please give a teaching.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:2.3"
msgid "“Na, bhaginī, kappati mātugāmassa dhammaṃ desetun”ti."
msgstr "“It’s not allowable for us to teach women.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:2.4"
msgid "“Iṅghāyyā, chappañcavācāhi dhammaṃ desetha, sakkā ettakenapi dhammo aññātun”ti."
msgstr "“Please just teach five or six sentences. Even with that much it’s possible to understand the Teaching.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:2.5"
msgid "“Na, bhaginī, kappati mātugāmassa dhammaṃ desetun”ti."
msgstr "“It’s not allowable for us to teach women.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:2.6"
msgid "Kukkuccāyantā na desesuṃ."
msgstr "And being afraid of wrongdoing, they did not teach them."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:2.7"
msgid "Upāsikā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "Then those female lay followers complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:2.8"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma, ayyā, amhehi yācīyamānā dhammaṃ na desessantī”ti."
msgstr "“How can they not teach us when asked?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8, ms2V_204
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:2.9"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tāsaṃ upāsikānaṃ ujjhāyantīnaṃ khiyyantīnaṃ vipācentīnaṃ."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of those female lay followers,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:2.10"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "and they told the Master."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:2.11"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards the Master gave a teaching and addressed the monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:2.12"
msgid "“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, mātugāmassa chappañcavācāhi dhammaṃ desetuṃ."
msgstr "“Monks, I allow you to teach five or six sentences to a woman."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:2.13"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:2.13a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second preliminary ruling"

#. HTML: </h3><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc9, ms2V_205
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:2.14"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhū mātugāmassa uttarichappañcavācāhi dhammaṃ deseyya, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk gives a teaching of more than five or six sentences to a woman, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p class="endsection">
#. REF: sc10, pts-vp-pli4.22, ms2V_206
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:2.15"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Third sub-story"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: sc11, pts-cs-bu-pc7.3, ms2V_207
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:3.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū—“bhagavatā anuññātaṃ mātugāmassa chappañcavācāhi dhammaṃ desetun”ti te aviññuṃ purisaviggahaṃ upanisīdāpetvā mātugāmassa uttarichappañcavācāhi dhammaṃ desenti."
msgstr "When the monks from the group of six knew that the Master had made this allowance, they taught women more than five or six sentences in the presence of a man who did not understand."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:3.2"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:3.3"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:3.4"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū aviññuṃ purisaviggahaṃ upanisīdāpetvā mātugāmassa uttarichappañcavācāhi dhammaṃ desessantī”ti."
msgstr "“How can the monks from the group of six teach women more than five or six sentences in the presence of a man who does not understand?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12, ms2V_208
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:3.5"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū chabbaggiye bhikkhū anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing those monks in many ways, they told the Master. …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:3.6"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, aviññuṃ purisaviggahaṃ upanisīdāpetvā mātugāmassa uttarichappañcavācāhi dhammaṃ desethā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:3.7"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:3.8"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:3.9"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, aviññuṃ purisaviggahaṃ upanisīdāpetvā mātugāmassa uttarichappañcavācāhi dhammaṃ desessatha."
msgstr "“… Foolish men, how can you teach women more than five or six sentences in the presence of a man who doesn’t understand?"

#. REF: pts-vp-en.2.206
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:3.10"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:3.11"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:3.11a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule"> 
#. VAR: uttarichappañcavācāhi → uttariṃ ­chappañ­cavācāhi (s1-3)
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:3.12"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu mātugāmassa uttarichappañcavācāhi dhammaṃ deseyya, aññatra viññunā purisaviggahena, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk gives a teaching of more than five or six sentences to a woman, except in the presence of a man who understands, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:4.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:4.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:4.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. HTML: </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:4.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:4.1.4"
msgid "… pe … ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "…The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc15, ms2V_211
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:4.1.5"
msgid "Mātugāmo nāma"
msgstr "A woman:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:4.1.6"
msgid "manussitthī; na yakkhī na petī na tiracchānagatā;"
msgstr "a human female, not a female spirit, not a female ghost, not a female animal;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:4.1.7"
msgid "viññū, paṭibalā subhāsitadubbhāsitaṃ duṭṭhullāduṭṭhullaṃ ājānituṃ."
msgstr "one who understands and is capable of discerning bad speech and good speech, what is lewd and what is not lewd."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc16, ms2V_212
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:4.1.8"
msgid "Uttarichappañcavācāhīti"
msgstr "More than five or six sentences:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:4.1.9"
msgid "atirekachappañcavācāhi."
msgstr "in excess of five or six sentences."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc17, ms2V_213
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:4.1.10"
msgid "Dhammo nāma"
msgstr "A teaching:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:4.1.11"
msgid "buddhabhāsito, sāvakabhāsito, isibhāsito, devatābhāsito, atthūpasañhito, dhammūpasañhito."
msgstr "what has been spoken by the Buddha, what has been spoken by disciples, what has been spoken by sages, what has been spoken by gods, what is connected with what is beneficial, what is connected with the Teaching."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc18, ms2V_214
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:4.1.12"
msgid "Deseyyāti"
msgstr "Gives:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:4.1.13"
msgid "padena deseti, pade pade āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "if he teaches by the line, then for every line he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:4.1.14"
msgid "Akkharāya deseti, akkharakkharāya āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If he teaches by the syllable, then for every syllable he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc19, ms2V_215
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:4.1.15"
msgid "Aññatra viññunā purisaviggahenāti"
msgstr "Except in the presence of a man who understands:"

# NOTE: “Is present” is not actually found in the Pali, but it is implied.
#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:4.1.16"
msgid "ṭhapetvā viññuṃ purisaviggahaṃ."
msgstr "unless a man who understands is present."

#. HTML: </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:4.1.17"
msgid "Viññū nāma"
msgstr "A man who understands:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:4.1.18"
msgid "purisaviggaho, paṭibalo hoti subhāsitadubbhāsitaṃ duṭṭhullāduṭṭhullaṃ ājānituṃ."
msgstr "one who is capable of discerning bad speech and good speech, what is lewd and what is not lewd."

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:4.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc20, pts-cs-bu-pc7.4.2, ms2V_216
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:4.2.1"
msgid "Mātugāme mātugāmasaññī uttarichappañcavācāhi dhammaṃ deseti, aññatra viññunā purisaviggahena, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it is a woman, and he perceives her as a woman, and he teaches her more than five or six sentences, except in the presence of a man who understands, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:4.2.2"
msgid "Mātugāme vematiko uttarichappañcavācāhi dhammaṃ deseti, aññatra viññunā purisaviggahena, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it is a woman, but he is unsure if it is, and he teaches her more than five or six sentences, except in the presence of a man who understands, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. REF: pts-vp-en.2.207
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:4.2.3"
msgid "Mātugāme amātugāmasaññī uttarichappañcavācāhi dhammaṃ deseti, aññatra viññunā purisaviggahena, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it is a woman, but he does not perceive her as a woman, and he teaches her more than five or six sentences, except in the presence of a man who understands, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc21, pts-vp-pli4.23, ms2V_217
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:4.2.4"
msgid "Yakkhiyā vā petiyā vā paṇḍakassa vā tiracchānagatamanussaviggahitthiyā vā uttarichappañcavācāhi dhammaṃ deseti, aññatra viññunā purisaviggahena, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he teaches more than five or six sentences to a female spirit, a female ghost, a sexual nonconformist, or a female animal in the form of a woman, except in the presence of a man who understands, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:4.2.5"
msgid "Amātugāme mātugāmasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is not a woman, but he perceives it as a woman, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:4.2.6"
msgid "Amātugāme vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is not a woman, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:4.2.7"
msgid "Amātugāme amātugāmasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr "If it is not a woman, and he does not perceive it as a woman, there is no offense."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:4.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc22, pts-cs-bu-pc7.4.3, ms2V_218
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:4.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:4.3.2"
msgid "viññunā purisaviggahena,"
msgstr "if a man who understands is present;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:4.3.3"
msgid "chappañcavācāhi dhammaṃ deseti,"
msgstr "if he teaches five or six sentences;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:4.3.4"
msgid "ūnakachappañcavācāhi dhammaṃ deseti,"
msgstr "if he teaches less than five or six sentences;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:4.3.5"
msgid "uṭṭhahitvā puna nisīditvā deseti,"
msgstr "if he gets up and then sits down again and teaches;"

# NOTE: _Tasmiṃ deseti_. According to [](Sp.4.751.8) this locative should be read as a dative.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:4.3.6"
msgid "mātugāmo uṭṭhahitvā puna nisīdati tasmiṃ deseti,"
msgstr "if the woman gets up and then sits down again, and he then teaches her;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:4.3.7"
msgid "aññassa mātugāmassa deseti,"
msgstr "if he teaches another woman;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:4.3.8"
msgid "pañhaṃ pucchati,"
msgstr "if he asks a question;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:4.3.9"
msgid "pañhaṃ puṭṭho katheti,"
msgstr "if he is asked a question and then speaks;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:4.3.10"
msgid "aññassatthāya bhaṇantaṃ mātugāmo suṇāti,"
msgstr "if he is speaking for the benefit of someone else and a woman listens in;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:4.3.11"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:4.3.12"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. HTML: </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc23, ms2V_219
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc7:4.3.13"
msgid "Dhammadesanāsikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ sattamaṃ."
msgstr "The seventh rule, the training rule on teaching, is finished."
